## Important Notes
1. Drain notification queue at start of each test
2. InMemory provider doesn't support concurrency tokens (RowVersion) — skip concurrency exception testing in DepartmentsController.Edit, just test the happy path
3. For DepartmentsController.Edit POST, use db.Entry(department).State = EntityState.Modified approach — the InMemory provider handles this fine for non-concurrent scenarios. IMPORTANT: The InMemory provider will throw InvalidOperationException if you try to attach an entity with the same key that's already tracked. Use a FRESH context or detach entities. Best approach: create entity in one context, then test Edit in a new context with the same DB name.
4. For InstructorsController.Edit POST (async with TryUpdateModelAsync) — skip this test as it requires full controller context with model binding. Test Edit GET instead.
5. For Delete with department admin nullification: seed an instructor as a department administrator, then delete the instructor, verify department.InstructorID becomes null.
6. Do NOT modify any existing test files

